task.summary:
Space Log Drains CLI Commands
This modifies/adds the following CLI commands:
- `heroku spaces:create --log-drain-url`: adds the new `--log-drain-url` flag to activate direct logging. Also requires a user pass. - `heroku drains:get --space SPACE`: gets the log drain for a space. spoke with product, and the decision was to keep this under the `drains` namespace like this for consistency. we might change it in the future and/or stick it in the space's info, but this is what we're going with for now. - `heroku drains:set URL --space SPACE`: replaces the log drain for a space. same caveat about the namespace. feedback of course is welcome, but wanted to get something out there to be able to use the feature.
Simplify spaces:wait output to match CLI style
Simplify spaces:wait output to match CLI style and de-dupe info code

Fix empty features parsing
If a user does not supply the `--features` flag, an empty string in an array (i.e.`[""]`) was being sent to API and failing with `Private Space features cannot be selected.`. This handles parsing the null/empty case fore features.
Note, I extracted out a `splitCsv()` function for this for better testing and reusablity. This should maybe belong the common CLI utils and/or the base CLI app as an option on the `flags`. Adding it here for now to fix the bug, but we can explore that later. cc: @dickyxxx
cc: @ricardochimal
